Are you looking for delicious food made to order by a wonderful family? Are you ready to be welcomed to their restaurant as if you are a beloved family member?  Let me be clear, this is not fast food. If you are there on a Friday or Saturday night then you will be transported to Puerto Rico by the owners wonderful singing and guitar. There are only 50 seats so plan accordingly. The food is not spicy hot, but richly seasoned. If you do go there definitely get the potatoe balls and the green hot sauce. On a personal note for people with food allergies I have a severe allergy to black pepper and they so very accommodating that this is one of my favorite places in the world.  Five stars does not due this place justice as I would rate it higher if I could. In reading other reviews of this restaurant you may see that one of the biggest complaints is wait time on your order...I see this as a compliment on the quality as they actually prepare each meal individually.
